<div style="font-family: 'Calibri'; text-align: justify; font-size:
14.54px;" align="justify">Dear Sir / Ma&rsquo;am,<br /><br /> Greetings
from IIM Lucknow!<br /><br /> We are coming up with a programme for 5days
on <b>"Finance for Non- Finance Executives"</b> scheduled from <b>February
11 - 15, 2019</b> at <b>IIM Lucknow Campus</b>.<br /><br />
<b>INTRODUCTION</b> :<br /> Finance impacts on all segments of
organizational activity. It acquires funds, allocates resources, and tracks
performance. It becomes the focal point for managerial attention, decision
making, and accountability. Methods utilized by finance people in making
financial decision are important and relevant to managers of other
functional areas in all types of organizations. Thus the role of finance is
all pervasive and has impact on the managerial decisions of non-finance
executives. It is an extremely useful programme for management
professionals for learning essentials of finance.<br /><br />
<b>CONTENTS</b> :<br /> The programme will cover the following broad areas:

<ul>
<li> Understanding and analysis of financial statements </li>
<li> Cost concepts and costing system </li>
<li> Profit planning and short-term decision making </li>
<li> Risk and return in financial management </li>
<li> Techniques of capital budgeting </li>
<li> Capital structure decision </li>
<li> Dividend decision </li>
<li> Working capital management </li>
<li> Financial derivatives </li>
<li> Capital market </li>
<li> International finance </li>
</ul>
<b>PROGRAMME DIRECTOR</b> :<br /><br /> <b>Dr. Prakash Singh</b> is a
Professor in the Finance &amp; Accounting area at IIM Lucknow. He holds a
Ph. D in "Reforms in Indian Banking" from BITS, Pilani, Rajasthan, besides
a B.E. in Mechanical Engineering from HBTI, Kanpur and an MBA in Finance
from Lucknow University. He is teaching courses in Commercial Bank
Management, Risk Management and Financial Institutions, Financial Reporting
and Valuation for Post Graduate students at IIM Lucknow.<br /><br />
<b>Prof. Ajay K Garg</b> is Associate Professor in Finance and Accounting
Area at the Indian Institute of Management Lucknow (IIML). He is an MBA in
Finance and has obtained his Doctoral degree from IIM Bangalore. He has
professional experience of 22 years. He has published articles in refereed
National and International Journals and has National and International
Conference presentations to his credit.<br /><br /> <b>PARTICIPANTS
PROFILE</b> :<br /><br /> This programme is designed for Heads of
Divisions/Functions, Middle Level Managers and Managers, who are new to the
concepts of finance or those who wish to update their knowledge on basic
Finance and Accounts.<br /><br /> <b>How to apply:</b> <ol
style="margin-top: 0px;">
